---
title: Veggie Baked Penne with Herbed Ricotta & Mozzarella
description: No matter the weather, it’s pretty much impossible not to daydream about cheesy baked carbs. Luckily, this dish is guaranteed to make those dreams come true. In it, you’ll find penne and zucchini layered with herby, creamy ricotta and a rich marinara sauce. To top things off, there’s a melty blanket of mozzarella. Serve it right from the dish for maximum cheese pull potential and wait for the oohs and aahs from your lucky fellow diners.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/veggie-baked-penne-d3100562.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/veggie-baked-penne-5e26044cb9721f76446c7589-d2c1af9e.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1020 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/veggie-baked-penne-5e26044cb9721f76446c7589
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim @zucchini{1}, then grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, diced) (save remaining for another use; dice whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @roma tomato{1}(finely diced).

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes}. Drain. Reserve empty pot for use in step 5.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion, tomato, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in @marinara cup{14%oz}, grated zucchini, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), @water{1/4%cup} (@water{1/2%cup} for 4 servings), @sugar{1%tsp} (@sugar{2%tsp} for 4), and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a simmer. Cook ~{2-4%minutes} more, then turn off heat.

While sauce simmers, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, remaining Italian seasoning, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tbsp} (@butter{2%tbsp} for 4 servings) to pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine. Spread out half the pasta mixture in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{}. (For 4 servings, use a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{}.) Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with seasoned ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Cover baking dish with #foil{}. (TIP: Spray inside of foil with nonstick spray first to prevent sticking.) Bake on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil. Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Let cool slightly, then top with @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Divide pasta between plates and serve.